<span id="Description"></span>
==Descrição==

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
The [[Image:BIM_Sketch.svg|24px]] [[BIM_Sketch|BIM Sketch]] tool creates a new sketch on the current [[Draft_SelectPlane|Working Plane]] and opens the [[Sketcher_Dialog|Sketcher Dialog]] to edit it.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
While the standard [[Sketcher_NewSketch|Sketcher NewSketch]] tool opens a dialog to select a base plane or maps to a selected face, the BIM Sketch tool is optimized for quicker BIM workflows. It ignores current selections and directly places the new sketch on the orientation and origin of the current [[Draft_SelectPlane|Working Plane]].
</div>

<span id="Usage"></span>
==Utilização==

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
# Ensure the [[Draft_SelectPlane|Working Plane]] is set to the desired orientation and position (e.g., set to a face or a level).
# There are several ways to invoke the tool:
#* Press the {{Button|[[Image:BIM_Sketch.svg|16px]] [[BIM_Sketch|Sketch]]}} button.
#* Select the {{MenuCommand|2D Drafting → [[Image:BIM_Sketch.svg|16px]] Sketch}} option from the menu.
#* Use the keyboard shortcut: {{KEY|S}} then {{KEY|K}}.
# The interface switches to the [[Sketcher_Workbench|Sketcher Workbench]] and the [[Sketcher_Dialog|Sketcher Dialog]] (task panel) opens.
# Create the desired geometry using the Sketcher tools.
# When finished, press the {{Button|Close}} button in the task panel.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
==Notes==
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* If you need to map a sketch to a specific face, use the standard [[Sketcher_NewSketch|Sketcher NewSketch]] tool or set the Working Plane to that face before using BIM Sketch.
* The sketch is automatically placed inside the active container (Project, Site, Building, or Level) in the [[Tree_View|Tree View]]. To place the sketch in a specific group or layer, use the [[Draft_AddToGroup|Draft AutoGroup]] command.
</div>

